been cutting traps?

46:24.552 --> 46:25.583
Really?

46:25.585 --> 46:27.689
Yeah, you don't be hearing that?

46:28.054 --> 46:29.056
Uh uh.

46:29.489 --> 46:30.456
Right Moe?

46:30.458 --> 46:32.560
You hear anything about traps
getting cut?

46:32.893 --> 46:34.830
No not that I know of, uh uh.

46:35.563 --> 46:36.795
No sir, nope.

46:36.797 --> 46:39.565
I know some of the other trappers
are struggling right now.

46:39.568 --> 46:41.567
- Yeah.
- And I even overheard Roscoe saying

46:41.570 --> 46:43.701
that he can't afford to get new
traps to start over.

46:43.703 --> 46:45.506
There you go again with your
doting baby.

46:45.873 --> 46:47.342
Everything cress, alright.

46:47.707 --> 46:49.910
Me and Malik just come from
doing a big haul.

46:50.143 --> 46:52.810
See me and Moe getting the chop
ready we're gonna head back out.

46:52.812 --> 46:54.681
Everything will be just fine
baby, OK?

46:54.982 --> 46:55.984
Trust me baby.

46:56.484 --> 46:58.585
These big hands can hold it all.

46:58.853 --> 47:00.054
OK, but you know,

47:01.155 --> 47:03.421
If we need I can take some
shifts at the bungalow.

47:03.423 --> 47:04.425
The only thing,

47:04.890 --> 47:06.057
we need,

47:06.059 --> 47:08.096
is for you to feel better baby.

47:09.528 --> 47:11.162
You gotta get plenty of rest,

47:11.164 --> 47:12.829
stay nice and healthy.

47:12.831 --> 47:15.101
And bring my progeny into the
world

47:16.001 --> 47:17.771
That's the future king of Taino.

47:18.038 --> 47:19.540
Nah, just the prince.

47:20.706 --> 47:22.642
His daddy's already the king.

47:24.145 --> 47:24.945
You know it.

47:25.711 --> 47:28.381
Look here, I want you go home,
rest up.

47:28.881 --> 47:30.580
Take a nice little bath.

47:30.582 --> 47:31.883
I'll be home later.

47:31.885 --> 47:33.486
Me and Moe can finish all this
work.

47:33.952 --> 47:34.818
OK well,

47:34.820 --> 47:37.021
- You ain't gotta tell me twice.
- Aaah.

47:37.023 --> 47:38.025
Bye bye Moe.

47:39.425 --> 47:41.991
You don't mind if I carry cap
for a drink.

47:41.993 --> 47:43.396
Like one, just one.

47:44.497 --> 47:46.430
- Or six!
- Man don't lie to her.

47:46.432 --> 47:48.701
More than six, I'll bring him
home.

48:05.116 --> 48:06.118
Cap.

48:08.754 --> 48:09.755
Cap?

48:12.024 --> 48:13.025
Naz.

48:14.025 --> 48:14.958
Cap!

48:14.960 --> 48:17.930
Oh come on man, talk to me man
it's Moe.

48:18.563 --> 48:21.000
Man whatever you need me to do,
you know I got yo' back.

48:22.500 --> 48:24.136
For you and the future king.

48:25.669 --> 48:26.671
Yo, Moe.

48:29.941 --> 48:32.007
We gonna have to build some
bigger traps brother.

48:33.745 --> 48:34.776
Let's head out!

48:34.778 --> 48:35.780
Let's do it!

48:37.081 --> 48:38.517
And I mean tonight!

48:46.090 --> 48:47.158
This is so cool.

48:48.059 --> 48:50.528
I can't believe it actually
worked.

48:50.995 --> 48:52.862
So did Echo really hear it?

48:52.864 --> 48:53.866
Oh yeah.

48:54.198 --> 48:55.598
He came right up to me.

48:55.600 --> 48:56.869
And as he got close,

48:57.568 --> 48:59.070
I could see him dancing.

49:01.071 --> 49:02.073
So,

49:03.073 --> 49:04.138
a p-a...

49:04.140 --> 49:05.744
a pod can...

49:06.077 --> 49:07.912
like faraway can hear this?

49:09.246 --> 49:10.449
Well,

49:10.980 --> 49:12.516
this is a little one.

49:15.218 --> 49:17.856
And Echo was only a hundred feet
away.

49:20.190 --> 49:21.223
I'll tell you what,

49:21.225 --> 49:22.824
Simmons was on to something.

49:22.826 --> 49:24.029
So he wasn't crazy.

49:28.765 --> 49:29.968
Maybe a good crazy.

49:35.606 --> 49:37.007
Alright, time for bed.

49:37.840 --> 49:38.842
Scoot down.

49:40.210 --> 49:41.309
There we go.

49:41.311 --> 49:44.145
Dad I've been reading a lot
about dolphins lately.

49:44.147 --> 49:44.978
Really?

49:44.980 --> 49:46.780
They speak their own language,
with

49:46.782 --> 49:48.650
clicking patterns to talk to
each other.

49:48.652 --> 49:51.222
- I didn't know that.
- I really hope the whistler works.

49:52.288 --> 49:54.023
Me too baby girl, me too.

49:56.226 --> 49:58.126
We are gonna find a way

49:58.128 --> 49:59.129
to get Echo,

49:59.328 --> 50:00.563
back with a pod.

50:00.964 --> 50:01.931
'Kay.

50:02.831 --> 50:04.234
You just need to believe in
yourself.

50:05.869 --> 50:07.101
I believe in you.

50:07.103 --> 50:08.201
Thanks dad.

50:08.203 --> 50:09.337
You're welcome.

50:24.319 --> 50:25.522
Hey dude.

50:30.626 --> 50:32.762
How do you even swim in your
sleep?

50:33.896 --> 50:35.798
You're in the water nonstop.

50:36.232 --> 50:39.769
Nova said you learned how to
swim before you were even born.

50:48.610 --> 50:50.077
Kind of like my mom did

50:51.346 --> 50:52.649
When I was a kid.

50:55.249 --> 50:57.019
She taught me how to swim.

51:01.256 --> 51:03.623
But ever since she passed I felt
like

51:03.625 --> 51:05.561
if I fall in I would sink.

51:14.336 --> 51:15.972
Think I would sink?

51:25.146 --> 51:26.148
What?

51:26.713 --> 51:27.715
What?

51:28.181 --> 51:29.183
Stop.

51:32.387 --> 51:33.589
Hey watch it!

51:35.722 --> 51:36.724
I'll... Ah.

51:38.159 --> 51:40.095
Yeah I know you want to play.

51:40.695 --> 51:41.963
But I can't. I just can't

51:44.965 --> 51:47.733
Can you just be serious for a
second?

51:47.735 --> 51:49.835
Echo I need your serious face.

51:49.837 --> 51:50.838
Seriously.

51:53.173 --> 51:54.175
Oh wow Echo.

51:54.442 --> 51:56.645
Thank you so much.

52:23.035 --> 52:25.236
Well who gets to swim with
a real life dolphin

52:25.238 --> 52:26.406
It's now or never.

52:27.006 --> 52:28.675
Don't let me fall under.

52:30.176 --> 52:31.178
I mean it dude.

52:45.225 --> 52:46.894
OK, this was a bad idea!

52:47.861 --> 52:48.863
Aaah!

52:52.332 --> 52:53.833
Well this was stupid!

52:58.336 --> 52:59.338
Ah!

53:35.374 --> 53:36.376
Not so bad.

53:36.808 --> 53:37.873
I gotta...

53:37.875 --> 53:38.776
I gotta tell dad.

53:42.847 --> 53:43.647
I was swimming!

54:37.034 --> 54:38.035
Luke!

54:42.939 --> 54:44.474
Hey you got in the water!

54:48.009 --> 54:49.343
I remember swimming with mom.

54:49.345 --> 54:50.146
It was amazing!

54:50.581 --> 54:52.316
I want to be back on the swim
team.

54:53.015 --> 54:54.048
Yes!

54:54.050 --> 54:56.018
That's what Im talking about.

54:56.285 --> 54:57.286
Come here.

55:00.891 --> 55:02.325
I'm proud of you buddy.

55:03.391 --> 55:04.528
Oh! Look at Echo!

55:04.994 --> 55:07.396
I guess you weren't swimming
alone were you?

55:08.297 --> 55:09.864
Probably wouldn't call it
swimming.

55:09.866 --> 55:12.537
Echo was probably doing circles
around you, huh?

57:23.764 --> 57:24.965
Hey cap.

57:26.265 --> 57:28.334
Looks like little man getting
close to that dolphin you know.

57:47.352 --> 57:48.319
Buddy,

57:48.321 --> 57:51.426
looks like our line ain't been
getting cut.

57:53.225 --> 57:54.660
It been getting chewed.

57:59.031 --> 58:00.598
Look like we might have to keep
an eye on

58:00.600 --> 58:02.265
Yankee boy with that
new fishy friend.

58:02.267 --> 58:04.470
- I'll keep an eye on him.
- Be sure you do that.

58:05.469 --> 58:08.006
Can't afford for no one to take
food out of our mouth.

58:08.240 --> 58:09.242
Not at all cap.

58:09.675 --> 58:10.774
Roger that.

58:10.776 --> 58:11.979
Leave it to me.

58:25.825 --> 58:27.361
Uhm...

58:28.293 --> 58:29.662
Guys I'm sorry the,

58:31.262 --> 58:32.999
the whistler didn't work.

58:33.764 --> 58:35.134
It's too corroded I can't,

58:35.333 --> 58:36.601
ugh, I can't figure it out

58:37.068 --> 58:39.038
what to do but I'm gonna keep
trying

58:39.371 --> 58:41.639
I want you to know that, and
just keep your head up.

58:42.107 --> 58:43.476
We'll figure this out.

59:56.346 --> 59:57.348
I have an idea!

01:00:01.416 --> 01:00:03.483
- Look right here look!
- Pipes are tied to the boat.

01:00:03.485 --> 01:00:04.851
We throw them overboard.

01:00:04.853 --> 01:00:06.220
So the pipes,

01:00:06.222 --> 01:00:07.387
- stay on the rope.
- OK.

01:00:07.389 --> 01:00:09.093
So they're hanging over the
side.

01:00:09.459 --> 01:00:10.926
Cause they're all tied
up to the things!

01:00:10.928 --> 01:00:12.526
Yeah that things!

01:00:12.528 --> 01:00:13.832
Yes the cleats!

01:00:14.230 --> 01:00:15.396
But all the cleats!

01:00:15.398 --> 01:00:17.564
Cause you're gonna need a lot of
pipes.

01:00:17.567 --> 01:00:19.200
Cause they all
gotta bang together.

01:00:19.203 --> 01:00:20.901
Yeah like, Bong! Bong!

01:00:20.903 --> 01:00:23.606
So the pipes are
hanging on the side of the boat.

01:00:23.840 --> 01:00:25.305
And we can
totally hear it

01:00:25.307 --> 01:00:26.840
when metal clangs underwater.

01:00:26.842 --> 01:00:29.342
So you know dolphins can
hear way better! Echo location!

01:00:29.344 --> 01:00:32.381
And Nova said they can
hear up to 200 meters away.

01:00:33.215 --> 01:00:34.749
And the Ocean is always moving.

01:00:34.751 --> 01:00:37.783
And the boat can just stay
at the opening to let the pipes play

01:00:37.785 --> 01:00:40.789
And jangle together so the
dolphins can hear.

01:00:42.492 --> 01:00:43.460
Like a chime.

01:00:44.860 --> 01:00:46.860
Exactly it'll do what
the whistler idea was meant to be.

01:00:46.862 --> 01:00:48.396
Well the whistler the clicks

01:00:48.398 --> 01:00:49.828
were in a musical rhythm, like

01:00:49.830 --> 01:00:51.531
Bump, bump bump, bump bump, bump
bump.

01:00:51.533 --> 01:00:53.501
What better music to a dolphin

01:00:53.503 --> 01:00:55.534
then the rhythm of the ocean.

01:00:55.536 --> 01:00:57.906
Okay, but guys wait a second.

01:00:59.741 --> 01:01:02.578
It seems a little far fetched
though right?

01:01:02.944 --> 01:01:04.148
No!

01:01:05.614 --> 01:01:08.351
Not after everything you guys
taught us.

01:01:11.252 --> 01:01:14.352
Uh, I think I'm gonna have to
go with the kids on this one guys.

01:01:14.354 --> 01:01:17.524
Uh, if we get to toe this
instrument out in front of Taino,

01:01:17.526 --> 01:01:18.990
east though, east of the
opening,

01:01:18.992 --> 01:01:20.896
away from all the big freight
noise.

01:01:21.562 --> 01:01:22.864
Yeah, I think it'll work.

01:01:23.332 --> 01:01:24.564
Be like, bait without a hook.

01:01:24.567 --> 01:01:27.333
Yeah man,
if a pods around they gonna hear it.

